Leonardo 0.4.0:
- [x] Add feedback bubble
- [x] Cleaned up and consolidated LlamaPress specific code that the user is not likely to change in their Rails application.
- [x] Additional default functionality like pagination, impersonation, etc.

0.4.0b:
- [x] Add paper_trail and rack_attack
- [x] Add bin script to run all rails_tests at once. `bin/rails_tests`

06/20/26 (overlay change, no image bump):
- [x] bin/update: replace merge-based upstream propagation with a path-scoped **allowlist sync**
      (`git checkout upstream/main -- <allowlist>`) — never `git merge`, so upstream can't silently
      rewrite a client's app. Union-merges `.gitignore`, force-untracks `.leonardo/instance.json`,
      and commits the sync scoped + guarded against unrelated staged work. Adds `--sync-only`.
- [x] v1 allowlist = `bin` + `rails/db/migrate` (smallest self-sustaining set; grows via a fleet
      divergence audit). Commit guard derived from the allowlist.
- [x] Add `test/bin_update_sync.sh` regression test (+ a fast docker-free CI job).
- [x] .gitignore: instance.json + update markers.